10 Section 1. Section 15-8-111, MCA, is amended to read:
11 "15-8-111. Appraisal -- market value standard -- exceptions. (1) All Except as otherwise provided,
12 all taxable property must be appraised at 100% of its market value except as otherwise provided. The market
13 value is the average of the market value for the year containing the general assessment day provided for in 15-
14 8-201 and the prior 9 years, but the average must exclude the lowest and highest yearly data in the period.
15 (2) (a) Market value is the value at which property would change hands between a willing buyer
16 and a willing seller, neither being under any compulsion to buy or to sell and both having reasonable knowledge
17 of relevant facts.
18 (b) If the department uses the cost approach as one approximation of market value, the
19 department shall fully consider reduction in value caused by depreciation, whether through physical
20 depreciation, functional obsolescence, or economic obsolescence.
21 (c) If the department uses the income approach as one approximation of market value and
22 sufficient, relevant information on comparable sales and construction cost exists, the department shall rely upon
23 the two methods that provide a similar market value as the better indicators of market value.
24 (d) Except as provided in subsection (4), the market value of special mobile equipment and
25 agricultural tools, implements, and machinery is the average wholesale value shown in national appraisal
26 guides and manuals or the value before reconditioning and profit margin. The department shall prepare
27 valuation schedules showing the average wholesale value when a national appraisal guide does not exist.
28 (3) (a) In valuing class four residential and commercial property described in 15-6-134, the
