21 Section 2. Section 15-23-205, MCA, is amended to read:
22 "15-23-205. Assessment -- how made. (1) The department shall assess the railroad transportation
23 property of all railroads operated in more than one county or more than one state as provided in this section.
24 Assessment must be made to the person owning or leasing or using the property and must be made upon the
25 entire railroad within the state.
26 (2) The department shall determine the value of the railroad system for the current year by
27 multiplying the base value of the railroad by the value change factor determined under subsection (3). The
28 department shall then determine the average market value for the year containing the general assessment day
- 4 - LC 1228

